+## [19.0.2.19.47] - 2026-06-19
+
+### Fixed
+
+- **#696 / #701 — salesperson importer crashed at module-level execution
+  (`NameError: _rep_users_from_display is not defined`).** The #696 SALESPERSON
+  WIRING block (which calls `_rep_users_from_display` / `_web_user_id` /
+  `build_user_canon_map` at module scope) was emitted in STEP 1d BEFORE those
+  helpers were defined; the Odoo-shell runs the importer body top-to-bottom, so the
+  `--full --domains orders` run on montalu PROD raised the NameError and rolled back
+  (watermark NOT advanced — no partial data). Moved the wiring to AFTER the resolver
+  helper definitions in both `orders/` and `quotes/importer_runtime.py` (regions stay
+  byte-identical). Added a module-level call-before-def regression test that the
+  isolated resolver-region exec could not catch. No behaviour change to the resolver.
+
